    "recap_url": "https://www.gobulldogs.com/news/2026/3/13/baseball-late-nevada-surge-sends-bulldogs-to-9-4-loss-in-mw-opener",
    "recap_headline": "Fresno State Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FRESNO, Calif. \u2013\nThe Nevada Wolf Pack used early power and a late offensive surge to defeat the Fresno State baseball team, 9\u20134, on Friday night at Pete Beiden Field at Bob Bennett Stadium in the Mountain West opener for both teams.\nWith the loss, Fresno State dropped to 7\u20139 overall and 0\u20131 in conference play, while Nevada improved to 9\u20136 and 1\u20130 in the Mountain West.\nGriffen Sotomayor\nled the Bulldogs offensively, going 3-for-4 with two home runs, three RBIs and three runs scored.\nJett Ruby\nadded two hits and an RBI, while\nBrady Hewitt\nfinished with two hits and a double.\nNevada starter Alvaro Castro earned the win after allowing three runs over five innings, while reliever Brainard picked up the save with four innings of work. Fresno State starter\nTyler Patrick\nwas charged with the loss.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nNevada jumped out to an early lead in the opening inning. After reaching on an error, the Wolf Pack capitalized with back-to-back home runs from Kwon and Matsuzaki to take a 3\u20130 advantage.\nFresno State answered in the bottom half when\nGriffen Sotomayor\nlaunched a solo home run to right field to put the Bulldogs on the board.\nThe Bulldogs tied the game in the third inning.\nBrady Hewitt\nsparked the rally with a ground-rule double before Sotomayor struck again, blasting a two-run homer to deep left to make it 3\u20133.\nNevada regained the lead in the fourth inning, taking advantage of a pair of defensive miscues and a run-scoring single from Blythe to go back in front 5\u20133.\nFresno State trimmed the deficit to one in the sixth inning when Sotomayor singled and later scored on an RBI single from\nJett Ruby\n, cutting the Wolf Pack lead to 5\u20134.\nNevada pulled away in the eighth inning. Matsuzaki led off with his second home run of the game, and the Wolf Pack added three more runs on a double by Harvey, a sacrifice fly from Quiban and an error that allowed another run to score, extending the lead to 9\u20134.\nThe Bulldogs put two runners aboard in the ninth but were unable to mount a comeback as Nevada closed out the series opener.\nNOTES\nGriffen Sotomayor\nrecorded his first multi-home run game of the season.\nSotomayor finished 3-for-4 with three runs and three RBIs.\nBrady Hewitt\ncollected two hits, including a double.\nJett Ruby\ndrove in a run with a sixth-inning single.\nFresno State committed three errors in the game.\nUP NEXT\nThe Bulldogs will continue the series against the Wolf Pack on Saturday, March 14, at 3:05 p.m. PT."
